# ReqSense AI вЂ” Master Build Prompt (v5, Final)

Give this entire file to your AI coding agent (Claude Code / Cursor / Copilot).
This is v3 with two rounds of deliberate changes on top:
1. Frontend styling moved to **Material UI (MUI)** instead of Tailwind CSS.
2. Three v3 items were cut as not-needed-yet: the Celery Beat vendor
   health-ping job, the Groq circuit breaker, and login gating on
   `email_verified`. All three are real patterns for later, not for v1 вЂ”
   see the specific notes at each section below for why.

The doc keeps v3's underlying philosophy throughout: it deliberately
excludes speculative architecture (repository/UOW layers, event buses,
CQRS, API gateways, OpenTelemetry, provider-interface abstractions, feature
flags) вЂ” those solve problems this app doesn't have at v1 and would cost
more agent-generated bugs than they prevent. Build exactly what's below.

---

## WHAT YOU ARE BUILDING

ReqSense AI вЂ” a full-stack web application where an AI agent called **ARIA**
sits between a software client and a developer during requirements gathering
sessions. ARIA conducts the conversation, detects contradictions in real
time, and auto-generates a Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
document at the end.

The system has 3 user roles, scoped under an organization:

- **Client** вЂ” chats with ARIA, explains what they want built
- **Developer** вЂ” watches session, reads SRS, manages change requests
- **Admin** вЂ” manages platform, views analytics

