## TECH STACK вЂ” EXACT

### Backend
- Python 3.11
- FastAPI
- PostgreSQL (via SQLAlchemy ORM + asyncpg)
- **Redis via `redis.asyncio`** (NOT `aioredis` вЂ” deprecated/merged upstream)
- ChromaDB (vector store) вЂ” backed by a persistent volume or hosted Chroma
  Cloud, never bare local disk on an ephemeral host
- Sentence Transformers вЂ” model: `all-MiniLM-L6-v2`
- Groq API вЂ” model: `llama-3.1-8b-instant` (verify current model
  availability before locking this in вЂ” check
  `https://console.groq.com/docs/models`)
- **Groq SDK called directly вЂ” NO LangChain**
- python-docx (SRS generation)
- SendGrid (email notifications, sent via Celery вЂ” never inline in a request)
- **PyJWT** for JWT (NOT `python-jose`)
- **argon2-cffi** for password hashing (NOT `passlib`+`bcrypt`)
- Pydantic v2
- Alembic (database migrations)
- uvicorn
- **Celery + Redis broker** вЂ” background jobs: SRS generation, embedding,
  impact analysis, email sending
- **boto3** (or `cloudflare-r2` client) вЂ” object storage for generated
  `.docx` files and Chroma persistence, if not using a hosted vector DB
- **slowapi** вЂ” rate limiting
- **sentry-sdk** вЂ” error tracking
- **tenacity** вЂ” retry/backoff for external API calls (Groq, SendGrid)

### Frontend
- React 18 + Vite
- **Material UI (MUI) v5** вЂ” `@mui/material`, `@mui/icons-material`,
  `@emotion/react`, `@emotion/styled` вЂ” this replaces Tailwind CSS as the
  styling/component system. One central `theme.js` defines palette,
  typography, and spacing; all components use MUI's `sx` prop or `styled()`
  rather than utility classes, so there is a single source of visual truth
  instead of two competing styling systems.
- React Router v6
- Axios
- Zustand (state management)
- Recharts (analytics charts) вЂ” MUI has no native charting; Recharts stays
- React Query (server state)
- Lucide React icons are dropped in favor of `@mui/icons-material`, so the
  icon set matches the component library instead of mixing two icon fonts
- Framer Motion (animations) вЂ” kept; MUI's built-in `Transition` components
  cover simple cases, Framer Motion stays for anything more custom
- react-hot-toast is dropped in favor of MUI's `Snackbar` + `Alert`, so
  notifications look native to the rest of the UI instead of being a
  visually separate library

### Deployment
- Backend: Render (Web Service + separate Background Worker service for
  Celery)
- Frontend: Vercel
- Database: Render PostgreSQL
- Redis: Render Redis (also used as Celery broker)
- Object storage: Cloudflare R2 or AWS S3 for `.docx` files and (if
  self-hosting Chroma) its persistence directory, attached via a Render
  Persistent Disk if you keep Chroma local
- Error tracking: Sentry (free tier is fine to start)

