## DATABASE SCHEMA вЂ” BUILD ALL THESE TABLES

*(unchanged from v3 вЂ” no frontend change affects the data layer)*

> All FK columns must have explicit indexes. Add `CREATE INDEX` statements in
> Alembic migrations for every `*_id` foreign key column below. Also add
> these composite indexes, which matter more than single-column FK indexes
> for this app's actual query patterns:
> `(session_id, created_at)` on messages, `(project_id, created_at)` on
> requirement_atoms, `(project_id, status)` on feature_status and
> change_requests.

### Table: organizations
```sql
id            UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
name          VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
created_at    TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
```

### Table: users
```sql
id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
organization_id UUID REFERENCES organizations(id)
name            VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
email           VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL
password_hash   VARCHAR(255)
role            VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL   -- 'client', 'developer', 'admin'
is_active       BOOLEAN DEFAULT true
email_verified  BOOLEAN DEFAULT false  -- tracked, not enforced (see auth_service.py note)
failed_login_attempts INTEGER DEFAULT 0
locked_until    TIMESTAMP
created_at      TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
updated_at      TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
```

### Table: refresh_tokens
```sql
id            UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
user_id       UUID REFERENCES users(id)
token_hash    VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
expires_at    TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
revoked       BOOLEAN DEFAULT false
created_at    TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
```

### Table: password_reset_tokens
```sql
id            UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
user_id       UUID REFERENCES users(id)
